# =============================================================================
# Palmart — Frontend (Next.js) environment template
# =============================================================================
#
# HOW TO USE
# ---------
# 1. Copy this file to `.env.local` (same directory). That file is gitignored.
# 2. Restart `next dev` / your process after any change.
# 3. Only variables prefixed `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` are exposed to the browser; others
#    are server-only (Route Handlers, Server Components, `fetch` to the API).
#
# BASE URLs
# ---------
# Use no trailing slashes on origins unless a variable’s comment says otherwise.
#
# RELATED
# -------
# Backend email/link base should match `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_BASE_URL` → see
# `backend/.env.example` → `APP_PUBLIC_FRONTEND_BASE_URL`.
# Routing constants (paths like /login, /shop) live in `lib/config.ts`, not here.
#
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Server → Java API (required for dashboard BFF proxy)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used by `app/api/v1/[[...path]]/route.ts` for server-side proxying and SSR
# storefront fetches. In production, point this at the hosted Java API.
#
BACKEND_ORIGIN=https://kiosk.zelisline.com

# Alternative name (same meaning) if your host already defines it:
# API_BACKEND_ORIGIN=https://kiosk.zelisline.com

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public app origin (browser URL of this Next app)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used for absolute links in emails (backend) and storefront canonical URLs /
# Open Graph. Must match what users type in the address bar for the admin app.
#
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auth / tenant (dashboard sign-in)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When the host is not a mapped tenant domain, the UI can send this UUID as
# X-Tenant-Id. Leave empty if you only use subdomain or host-based tenancy.
#
NEXT_PUBLIC_TENANT_ID=

# Refresh tokens are httpOnly cookies on the API origin (ub.refresh). The browser
# sends them via credentials: 'include' on auth/API calls. If the frontend talks
# to the Java API directly (not the Next BFF proxy), CORS must allow credentials
# and backend APP_AUTH_REFRESH_COOKIE_* must match your deployment domain.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: browser calls API directly (needs CORS on the Java API)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# On https://palmart.co.ke the browser uses https://kiosk.zelisline.com via
# `apiUrl()` / `getApiBaseUrl()`. For local dev against a local API, set:
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5050
#
# WebSocket target (REQUIRED for cloud deployments).
#
# The browser opens the WebSocket directly on the Java API origin. Next.js
# rewrites CANNOT proxy WebSocket upgrades, so this must NOT be the Next.js
# frontend origin (e.g. do not use https://kiosk.zelisline.com if that host
# is served by Vercel). Point it at the Java API origin instead:
#
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_REALTIME_WS_ORIGIN=https://api.zelisline.com
#
# If this variable is unset, the client falls back to NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL
# and then to the hardcoded REMOTE_API_ORIGIN. When any of those fallbacks
# share the page host, the connection will usually fail with code 1006 and the
# client will fall back to REST polling (slower, and only for notifications).
NEXT_PUBLIC_REALTIME_WS_ORIGIN=https://kiosk.zelisline.com

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Phase 15 — public storefront (homepage strip + /shop + PDP)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Slug resolution order for /shop pages (see `frontend/lib/storefront-slug.ts`):
#   1. NEXT_PUBLIC_STOREFRONT_SLUG (explicit override; pins ALL hosts to one shop)
#   2. `<slug>.localhost` convention for local dev (e.g. kiosk.localhost:3000)
#   3. Backend lookup at GET /api/v1/public/host/resolve?host=<Host>
#      Any custom domain or platform subdomain that has an active row in the
#      `domains` table maps to its tenant.
#
# Leave NEXT_PUBLIC_STOREFRONT_SLUG UNSET in production so each mapped domain
# resolves to its own tenant via (3). Set it only for single-tenant staging
# previews or when you want one specific shop regardless of hostname.
#
# Storefront must also be enabled in business settings with a valid catalog
# branch, or the public catalog endpoints 404.
#
# Server-side `fetch()` uses BACKEND_ORIGIN above (not NEXT_PUBLIC_*).
# OpenAPI (contract): `backend/docs/openapi/phase-15-storefront-public.yaml`.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_STOREFRONT_SLUG=my-shop-slug

# Digits only, international format without + (used for wa.me link on PDP).
# Leave unset to hide the green “Ask on WhatsApp” button.
#
NEXT_PUBLIC_STOREFRONT_WHATSAPP=254712345678

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudinary (optional — only if you run image tooling from the frontend)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Product uploads are normally handled by the Java API. If this app needs
# Cloudinary client-side, set a URL from the Cloudinary dashboard (API Keys):
# cloudinary://<api_key>:<api_secret>@<cloud_name>
#
# CLOUDINARY_URL=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# - Subdomain handoff: after login on bare localhost, redirects may use
#   `{slug}.{NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_BASE_URL host}` — see auth handoff flow in the app.
# - Product photos: prefer enabling Cloudinary on the backend (`backend/.env`,
#   `APP_MEDIA_*`). See `backend/.env.example` and `application.properties`.
